title: Anderson Bruford Wakeman Howe Self Titled Album 1989 FLAC
description:
Anderson Bruford Wakeman Howe Self Titled Album 1989 FLAC

Anderson Bruford Wakeman Howe is the only studio album recorded by 
the English progressive rock band Anderson Bruford Wakeman Howe, 
released on 20 June 1989 on Arista Records.

Tracklist:

01 - Themes- i. Sound; ii. Second Attention; iii. Soul Warrior
02 - Fist Of Fire
03 - Brother Of Mine- i. The Big Dream; ii. Nothing Can Come Between Us; iii. Long Lost Brother of Mine
04 - Birthright
05 - The Meeting
06 - Quartet- i. I Wanna Learn; ii. She Gives Me Love; iii. Who Was the First; iv. I'm Alive
07 - Teakbois
08 - Order Of The Universe- i. Order Theme; ii. Rock Gives Courage; iii. It's So Hard to Grow; iv. The U
09 - Let's Pretend

Total Time = 59:05

Anderson Bruford Wakeman Howe:
Jon Anderson – lead vocals, production
Bill Bruford – acoustic and electronic drums (Tama and Simmons SDX, Paiste metals)
Rick Wakeman – keyboards (Roland and Korg)
Steve Howe – guitars (Gibson and Martin)
